about() {
    whiptail --title "About This Project" --msgbox "
    	This project is a simple command-line and dialog-based tool built with Bash.
        It allows system administrators to manage users and groups easily through
        interactive menus using the Whiptail interface.

        Main Features:
        • Add, modify, delete, and list users.
        • Add, modify, delete, and list groups.
        • Enable (unlock) or disable (lock) user accounts.
        • Clear and user-friendly interface with validation messages.


        Technologies Used:
        • Bash scripting
        • Whiptail (for graphical text-based menus)
        • Linux user & group management commands
    " 20 60
}

